      "source": [
        "# Welcome to Arctic Fox!"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "6bf4861d",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Arcitc Fox is a code autoamtion tool for reusable, sharable, and customizable automations!"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "3590343d",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "### What's an Automation?"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "15987681",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "A comment in code that follows this pattern:\n",
        "\n",
        "```python\n",
        "#[AutomationName ...]\n",
        "```\n",
        "\n",
        "In code files Arctic Fox formats the comments so that they look like the line below."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "27120324",
      "metadata": {},
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "#[ExampleAutomation --someParameter someValue]#@34119780"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "28482985",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Hello World!"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "17ed380f",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "As with all software development we'll start with a Hello World example! Follow these steps to use an automation to print out Hello World!\n",
        "\n",
        "- Open Sandbox.py if not already open\n",
        "- Add an automation, click into the file and press: ctrl+a\n",
        "  - This should have created the automation brackets\n",
        "- Within the brackets, type: HelloWorld\n",
        "- Move off the line, Arctic Fox should write: print(\"Hello World!\")\n",
        "\n",
        "[Compare to Sandbox.py Solution](./../Solutions/SolutionStep1.py)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "80228387",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Behind the Scenes?!"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "50804686",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "So what's happening hear? Open the HelloWorld.py file under the Autoamtions folder. Take a look at the file, check it out, and feel free to ask questions! Take note of the item/variable name. We'll use it next. "
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "76576970",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Pass in an Item"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "13006031",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Let's pass a name into the HelloWorld automation. Go back to the HelloWorld.py file. Add to the text within the brackets: --name YourNameHere. Move off the line, and Arctic Fox should rewrite the code to welcome you!\n",
        "\n",
        "[Compare to Sandbox.py Solution](./../Solutions/SolutionStep2.py)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "1e07fddf",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "# Done!"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "22f0df9c",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "Great! Let's go to the next. Ask any questions before moving on!"
      ]
    }
